  "_notes": "Senior men's titles, verified June 2026 against Wikipedia per-competition winners + per-team honours pages. Lineage: CZE includes Czechoslovakia (Euro 1976); GER includes West Germany; Soviet Union titles assigned to nobody. AFCON 2025 (Dec 2025-Jan 2026): Senegal won 1-0 on the pitch but CAF overturned it to a Morocco 3-0 forfeit win on 17 Mar 2026, so 2025 is credited to MAR (contested; Senegal's CAS appeal unresolved as of June 2026). AFC Asian Cup '2023' was played Jan-Feb 2024 (Qatar). CONCACAF Gold Cup counts merge the predecessor CONCACAF Championship (1963-1989). Confederations Cup includes retroactively-recognised King Fahd Cup editions. Nations League years use the finals/completion year. Teams with no covered title are omitted: AUT, BEL, BIH, CPV, CRO, CUW, ECU, JOR, NOR, PAN, SCO, SUI, SWE, TUR, UZB."
